ith excellent faculty, the result is unlimited possibilities. Upon graduation, great students become society's next change agents — the business and community leaders with the drive and collaborative spirit needed to solve the world's most pressing problems. Giving opportunities that support student scholarships and programs Scholarship Support makes college possible for deserving undergraduate and graduate students and student athletes The Honors College enriches the undergraduate experience for UNT's most academically talented students Student Affairs offers services, programs and activities to help students get involved in campus life, gain support and make memories at UNT Undergraduate Studies provides services designed to help ease the college transition Contact Information Contact Information University of North Texas Division of Advancement 1155 Union Circle #311250 Denton, Texas 76203-5017 Phone: (940) 565-2900 Toll Free: (800) 868-1153 TTY: (940) 369-8652 Email Us Email Us For questions about content in this web site, contact advancement@unt.edu. UNT System UNT System UNT System UNT Dallas Campus UNT Health Science Center Site last updated on: Disclaimer | AA/EOE/ADA | Privacy | Web Accessibility | State of Texas Online | Emergency Preparedness | THECB Online Resume System   